ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: What is the most you have ever weighed since reaching your current height (do not count any weight gains due to medical conditions or medication)? The most I have weighed since reaching my current height is (in pounds):
Weight lbs
Notes: "Weight change greater than 30 percent from baseline will be flagged as an adverse event. Field should not be left blank. If missing, please use -7,-8, -9."

ElementDescription: Please determine the difference between the most you have weighed and current weight.
Notes: lbs

ElementDescription: Please determine the difference between the most you have weighed and current weight. If this difference is 5 lbs. or more, indicate which of the three following statements describe you best:
Notes: A = The difference between my highest weight and my current weight is due to weight that I lost on purpose; B = The difference between my highest weight and my current weight is due to weight I lost even though I wasn't trying to; C = I'm not sure why I weigh less than I once did; 999 = question not answered (difference < 5 lbs)

ElementDescription: For about how long have you been at or close (within 2 lbs.) to your present weight?
Which of these statements best describes what has happened to your weight during the past 6 months?
Notes: 1 = My weight has stayed about the same; 2 = I've been losing weight; 3 = I've been gaining weight; 4 = My weight has fluctuated a lot

ElementDescription: Are you currently on a diet
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: Are you currently dieting to lose weight or to avoid gaining weight?
Notes: 1 = To lose weight; 2 = To avoid gaining weight; -999 = N/A or Missing

ElementDescription: Have you ever been on a diet to control your weight?
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes; 999 = Question not answered

ElementDescription: Abot how old were you when you went on your first diet?
Notes: Age in years; -999 = N/A or Missing

ElementDescription: Please estimate as best you can the number of times in your life you have dieted and lost 1-4 pounds
Please estimate as best you can the number of times in your life you have dieted and lost 5-10 pounds
Please estimate as best you can the number of times in your life you have dieted and lost 11-15 pounds
Please estimate as best you can the number of times in your life you have dieted and lost 16 or more pounds.

How old were you when you first engaged in binge eating (i.e., distinct eating episodes in which you experience a sense of loss of control over your eating and eat what you consider an excessive amount of food)?
Notes: Age in years

ElementDescription: How old were you when you first used exercise to compensate for a binge eating episode or in an effort to influence your weight or shape?
